main event: Observation of an unidentified aerial object over Englewood, Colorado on February 21, 1967.
interesting points: The observer described the object as a peach-colored, round object resembling the size of a basketball., The object was stationary in the western sky and remained visible for about 5 minutes., There was no sound associated with the object during the observation., The object's trajectory indicated it was heading southwest toward the mountains, and it disappeared beneath the horizon., The sighting was consistent with characteristics of an astronomical satellite, according to analysis.
sighted object: one round peach-colored object in the sky
